<body>
  <h1 class="header">Task One</h1>
  <h1 id="welcomeTaskOne"></h1>
  <h2>Task</h2>
  <p style="white-space:pre;">Make a playlist of 9 songs to listen to&nbsp;<span style="color:white">when traveling</span>&nbsp(e.g. commuting, etc.).
    <p id="likedisliketask1">Click&nbsp<i class="fa fa-thumbs-up"></i>&nbspor&nbsp<i class="fa fa-thumbs-down"></i>&nbspto keep or dismiss a song.</p>
  </p>
  <h2>Brief summary</h2>
  <p>
    <ol>
      <li>Select up to 5 of your favorite artists</li>
      <li>Adjust music attributes</li>
      <li>Click on the "Calculate recommendations" button</li>
      <li>Listen to a song of the recommended list</li>
      <li>Click thumbs-up or -down to keep or dismiss a song</li>
      <li>Repeat steps 2 to 5 until you have made a list of 9 songs</li>
      <li>Click on the "Save Recommendations" button</li>
    </ol>
  </p>
  <h2>Music Attributes</h2>
  <p>The system also let you interact with five different music attributes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Energy
      <p style="white-space:pre;" class="parLegend">Energy represents a perceptual measure of intensity and activity. Typically, energetic tracks feel fast, loud, and noisy.</p>
    </li>
    <li>Valence
      <p style="white-space:pre;" class="parLegend">A measure describing the musical positiveness conveyed by a track. Tracks with high valence sound more positive, while tracks with low valence sound more negative.</p>
    </li>
    <li>Acousticness
      <p style="white-space:pre;" class="parLegend">A confidence measure whether the track is acoustic. 100 represents high confidence the track is acoustic.</p>
    </li>
    <li>Instrumentalness
      <p style="white-space:pre;" class="parLegend">Predicts whether a track contains no vocals. Values above 50 are intended to represent instrumental tracks, but confidence is higher as the value approaches 100.</p>
    </li>
    <li>Danceability
      <p style="white-space:pre;" class="parLegend">Danceability describes how suitable a track is for dancing. 100 represents high confidence the track is danceable.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul><button id="task1" class="ripple button">Start</button></body>

